Started playing Animal Crossing for the GameCube once again. It does feel a lot more slow paced and comfy compared to the later series but I do miss some of the QOL changes the later series brought in.

>>208dd809-ddb2-4d13-b7a6-17d269401469

>>66a3a15f-1fce-4458-a256-8b0f0e0ea03f
I haven't been keeping up either with the emulation scene either. I do know the Wii U and Switch emulation has gotten better but its all based around BOTW. I've only really messed with emulation as high as the 6th generation for GameCube (which is still good) and PS2 (which is still crap).

>>fa2cdf1c-aa7f-42b7-9dbe-686d58f61a7c
Mostly people head towards projects that can either bring in donations or increase their E-peen with little effort. Thus the poor PS2 still suffers since its difficult to work with. It can still run things, performance is still suffering as once you get enough on screens games will have their FPS plummet. There is love still being put towards it, just not a lot of people willing to actually do it so progress is slow.

>>8d92936d-17a9-4a61-9393-a90c53a23a48
